# sideral curated flatpak remotes. Read by os/build.sh at image build
# (to register + preinstall the curated set into /var/lib/flatpak) and
# by sideral-flatpak-install.service on every boot (idempotent re-add,
# so deployed systems pick up new remotes added in future image rebases).
# Format:
#   <name>  <url-or-flatpakrepo>
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.

# Flathub — primary community flatpak distribution.
flathub  https://dl.flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo

# Fedora Flatpak registry (Fedora-built, signed flatpaks).
fedora   oci+https://registry.fedoraproject.org

# Helium has no remote here on purpose. The community community-packaged
# Helium project (MarioGK/helium-flatpak) advertises an ostree archive-z2
# remote at https://mariogk.github.io/helium-flatpak/, but the deployed
# GH Pages site only serves the .flatpakrepo descriptor and an empty
# summary — no objects/refs are actually published, so `flatpak install`
# from that remote fails ("Nothing matches net.imput.helium"). MarioGK
# ships working `.flatpak` release bundles instead, and os/build.sh
# installs the latest bundle at image build (no remote → image rebuilds
# are the helium update cadence; the other curated flatpaks still update
# via standard `flatpak update`).
